<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-07-17"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Gresham directs Mr. Baker to report without delay when the control of
                            the executive power of Nicaragua shall pass with general acquiescence to
                            any government, and to maintain an attitude of impartiality during the
                            deeply deplored continuance of civil dissensions in that country.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>